verbose_text: The prediction model was constructed using all 303 patients, based on age, sex, character of chest pain, resting systolic blood pressure on admission, serum cholesterol level, fasting blood glucose> 120 mg/dl, resting electrocardiograph, maximum heart rate achieved during exercise, exercise induced angina, ST segment depression during exercise, slope of the ST segment during peak exercise, number of calcified vessels detected by fluoroscopy, and the result of an exercise thallium scintigraphy test.
